<li id="cite_note-CJ-27">^ <a href="#cite_ref-CJ_27-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-CJ_27-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> Dean, Micheal. <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.tcj.com/234/n_sim.html">"In the Company of Sim"</a>. <i><a href="The_Comics_Journal" title="The Comics Journal">The Comics Journal</a></i>. 2001</li>
<li id="cite_note-28"><b><a href="#cite_ref-28">^</a></b> Sim, Dave. <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.theabsolute.net/misogyny/tangents.html">"Tangent"</a>. TheAbsolute.net</li>
<li id="cite_note-29"><b><a href="#cite_ref-29">^</a></b> <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://archives.tcj.com/263/e_stephen.html">Stephen, R.S.; "Masculinity's Last Hope, or Creepily Paranoid Misogynist? An Open Letter to Dave Sim"; tcj.com; Reprinted from <i>The Comics Journal</i> #263</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-30"><b><a href="#cite_ref-30">^</a></b> <span class="citation web"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.comicsalliance.com/2012/02/02/spawn-compendium-20-years-todd-mcfarlane/">"Spawn 20 Years Later: Looking Back at the Quintessential '90s Comic Book;"</a>. Comics Alliance. 2012-02-02<span class="printonly">. <a rel="nofollow" class="external free" href="http://www.comicsalliance.com/2012/02/02/spawn-compendium-20-years-todd-mcfarlane/">http://www.comicsalliance.com/2012/02/02/spawn-compendium-20-years-todd-mcfarlane/</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved 2012-02-03</span>.</span><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Spawn+20+Years+Later%3A+Looking+Back+at+the+Quintessential+%2790s+Comic+Book%3B&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.date=2012-02-02&amp;rft.pub=Comics+Alliance&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.comicsalliance.com%2F2012%2F02%2F02%2Fspawn-compendium-20-years-todd-mcfarlane%2F&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Dave_Sim"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-picofdavesformletter-31">^ <a href="#cite_ref-picofdavesformletter_31-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-picofdavesformletter_31-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <span class="citation web">Sim, Dave. <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/stanleylieber/2460581228/">"Dave Sim's form letter"</a><span class="printonly">. <a rel="nofollow" class="external free" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/stanleylieber/2460581228/">http://www.flickr.com/photos/stanleylieber/2460581228/</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved December 5, 2011</span>.</span><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Dave+Sim%27s+form+letter&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.aulast=Sim&amp;rft.aufirst=Dave&amp;rft.au=Sim%2C%26%2332%3BDave&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.flickr.com%2Fphotos%2Fstanleylieber%2F2460581228%2F&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Dave_Sim"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-TCJ52-25-32"><b><a href="#cite_ref-TCJ52-25_32-0">^</a></b> <a href="Kim_Thompson" title="Kim Thompson">Thompson, Kim</a>. "Good Aardvark Art", page 25. <i><a href="The_Comics_Journal" title="The Comics Journal">The Comics Journal</a></i> #52 (pages 25–27). <a href="Fantagraphics_Books" title="Fantagraphics Books">Fantagraphics Books</a>, December 1979</li>
<li id="cite_note-33"><b><a href="#cite_ref-33">^</a></b> <a rel="nofollow" class="external free" href="https://facultystaff.richmond.edu/~jwight/NCEE/Ethics%20and%20Economics.Wight.ppt">https://facultystaff.richmond.edu/~jwight/NCEE/Ethics%20and%20Economics.Wight.ppt</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-34"><b><a href="#cite_ref-34">^</a></b> <span class="citation web"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://archives.tcj.com/index.php?option=com_content&amp;task=view&amp;id=72&amp;Itemid=70">"The Comics Journal - The Comics Journal Performs a Public Service"</a>. Archives.tcj.com. 1999-10-08<span class="printonly">. <a rel="nofollow" class="external free" href="http://archives.tcj.com/index.php?option=com_content&amp;task=view&amp;id=72&amp;Itemid=70">http://archives.tcj.com/index.php?option=com_content&amp;task=view&amp;id=72&amp;Itemid=70</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved 2011-07-18</span>.</span><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=The+Comics+Journal+-+The+Comics+Journal+Performs+a+Public+Service&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.date=1999-10-08&amp;rft.pub=Archives.tcj.com&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Farchives.tcj.com%2Findex.php%3Foption%3Dcom_content%26task%3Dview%26id%3D72%26Itemid%3D70&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Dave_Sim"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-35"><b><a href="#cite_ref-35">^</a></b> "Just to be clear on the subject of what I consider scripture: the Torah, that is, the Law and the Prophets as held by Orthodox Judaism (i.e. no Ruth, no Esther, no Daniel, no Job, no Song of Songs, etc.), the First Book of Moshe through to Malachi, the four Gospels, Acts and John's Apocalypse, and all of the Koran." Sim, Dave. (2007) <i>Collected Letters Volume 2</i>, p. 90.</li>
<li id="cite_note-36"><b><a href="#cite_ref-36">^</a></b> <span class="citation web"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.backporchcomics.com/space.htm">"SPACE"</a>. BackPorchComics.com<span class="printonly">. <a rel="nofollow" class="external free" href="http://www.backporchcomics.com/space.htm">http://www.backporchcomics.com/space.htm</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved 2011-07-18</span>.</span><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=SPACE&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.pub=BackPorchComics.com&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.backporchcomics.com%2Fspace.htm&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Dave_Sim"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
